Lucius Cornelius Sulla, of a patrician family. Born 138. 107, Quae stor, served in Africa under Marius. Also served against the Teutone and Cimbri. 93, Praetor. 92, Propraetor in Cilicia. 90-89‚ took an active part iu the Social war. 88, Consul, entrusted with command in the Mith- ridatiowar, expelled from Romeby Marius, returned and drove Marius out. 87, set out for the East, spent three years in subduing it. 88, re turned to Italy and gained decided victorias over the Mar-ian party.- 82, fought a decisive battle at the Oolliue gate of Rome, thereby becoming master of Rome and Italy. Began his proscriptione. appointed Dicta· tor for an indefinite time. 80, Consul. 79, resigned dictatorship and retiredto Puteoli. 78, died at the age of sixty. During his dictatorship he affected many important changes in the Roman constitution.
